President Cyril Ramaphosa has called on women never tire from talking about the challenges they face every day. The President says South African government will continue to empower women. President Ramaphosa says government is working on implementing reforms that are going to ensure that the civil servant practice the principle “people first” when doing their jobs. Ramaphosa was speaking at the ANC Woman League fund Golf Day held in Blue Valley Golf Estate, centurion. This is an effort by the ANC Woman’ League to raise more money to intensify programs and campaigns to fight violence against woman and children. On this video below, is the ANC Women’s League Presidential Gala Dinner: 